  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to pay someone I find interesting so that I can send them a message.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Feature summary*: \r\nSee the [#096 Tribute to Talk idea](https://github.com/status-im/ideas/pull/165) for context.\r\n\r\nUser A does not have User B in their contact list. User A has a minimum tribute of 200 SNT set for non-contacts to message them.\r\n\r\nWhen User B starts a new chat with User A, they receive a system message asking for the minimum tribute.\r\n\r\nUser B then completes a transaction flow to send User A the tribute. Once confirmed, User B may send their message.\r\n\r\n*Implementation*:\r\nThe scope of this issue is to code the UI only. Values can be hard coded. \r\n\r\nRequest transaction messages require updating. (https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/4136)\r\n\r\n[System messages are being updated](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/3901), and #3233 and #3234 will add ERC20 support to chat. For this issue, we can work with existing system messages.\r\n\r\n#### Mockups\r\n[InVision prototype](https://projects.invisionapp.com/share/P5HQFU23BNA#/screens/294312819) - Zeplin screens TK\r\n\r\n![request flow 01](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15470435/39350363-8a742108-4a30-11e8-8a8d-ba18df2a0700.png)\r\n\r\n#### Additional Information\r\n\r\n[TtT contract documentation](https://github.com/status-im/contracts/blob/096-tribute-to-talk/TributeToTalk.md#contract-deployment)\r\n",
